 that HCN oligomers react with guanidine and formic acid to yield aminopyrimidines that are formylated to FaPy intermediates; this forms the chemical entry to Carell's base-on-sugar route for guanosine (Becker et al., 2016; Becker et al., 2018)."}, {"id": "rxn_015", "name": "Nitrite-driven dry-state enrichment and reduction to guanine FaPy intermediate", "inputs": ["mol_018", "mol_019", "mol_017"], "outputs": ["mol_018"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["elemental iron (Fe0)", "montmorillonite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "dry-state geothermal cycling", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "Fe0", "aqueous": "false", "other": "dry nitrosation then reduction with Fe/Ni in dilute formic acid; sequential precipitation enrichment"}, "mechanism": "Aminopyrimidine/FaPy precursor pools undergo dry-state nitrosation and are reduced by Fe/Ni in dilute formic acid to the reactive guanine-forming FaPy species, while precipitation enriches the desired intermediates.", "reasoning": "Becker et al. 2018 showed that dry-state nitrosation with sodium nitrite followed by reduction with elemental iron and nickel in dilute formic acid yields FaPys suitable for purine nucleoside synthesis under wet-dry cycles. This reaction is represented as an activating/enrichment transformation within the same FaPy hub node (Becker et al., 2018)."}, {"id": "rxn_016", "name": "Dry-state condensation of guanine FaPy precursor with ribose to guanosine", "inputs": ["mol_018", "mol_015"], "outputs": ["mol_021"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "373K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "null", "aqueous": "false", "other": "dry-state condensation near 100C followed by basic rehydration; ~60% N9-selective yield"}, "mechanism": "The purine ring is completed on a pre-associated sugar scaffold: FaPy condenses with ribose in the dry state, then rehydrates under basic conditions to furnish N9-selective guanosine.", "reasoning": "This is the central Carell breakthrough solving the purine glycosylation problem, giving ~60% N9-selective guanosine from guanine-directed FaPy intermediates and ribose (Becker et al., 2016)."}, {"id": "rxn_017", "name": "Base-first glycosylation of guanine with ribose to guanosine", "inputs": ["mol_014", "mol_015"], "outputs": ["mol_021"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "variable, drying-rehydration", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "null", "aqueous": "true", "other": "very low yield; included as contrast to FaPy pathway"}, "mechanism": "Direct condensation of free guanine with ribose forms guanoside linkage inefficiently because of low guanine solubility and regiochemical competition.", "reasoning": "Direct guanine glycosylation is a major bottleneck and low-yield pathway, but it is documented in prebiotic nucleotide studies as an inefficient alternative that the FaPy route overcomes. Included because the literature explicitly frames this as the key challenge and benchmark (Kim & Benner, 2017; Becker et al., 2016)."}, {"id": "rxn_018", "name": "Phosphorylation of guanosine to GMP", "inputs": ["mol_021", "mol_022"], "outputs": ["mol_023"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "ambient to mild heating", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "null", "aqueous": "true", "other": "geothermal cycling; prebiotic phosphate activation context"}, "mechanism": "Guanosine is phosphorylated at the 5'-position under prebiotic phosphate-rich cycling conditions to yield guanosine monophosphate.", "reasoning": "Becker et al. 2019 reported unified prebiotic synthesis of all four nucleosides plus their 5'-mono- and diphosphates under geochemically coherent conditions. This reaction extends guanine chemistry into nucleotide space and anchors the biochemical stage (Becker et al., 2019)."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Classical HCN oligomerization to guanine via cyanogen", "description": "HCN is concentrated in surface settings, oligomerized to DAMN, photoconverted to AICN, hydrolyzed to AICA, then annulated with cyanogen to guanine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_006"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "HCN oligomerization to guanine via cyanate", "description": "Same HCN trunk, but AICA reacts with cyanate as alternative ring-closing reagent toward guanine branch.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_007"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "HCN oligomerization to guanine in urea-rich drying system", "description": "HCN-derived AICA-like branch chemistry proceeds under urea-ammonium-formate drying conditions to guanine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Hydrothermal-to-surface formamide route with pyrite catalysis", "description": "Hydrothermal C1 reduction generates formamide-compatible feedstocks that, once concentrated at the surface, yield guanine by thermal formamide chemistry on iron-sulfur minerals.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Hydrothermal-to-surface UV formamide route", "description": "Hydrothermal reduced carbon is transferred as formamide feedstock, then UV-irradiated neat formamide at 130C yields guanine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "TiO2 photocatalytic formamide route", "description": "Adsorbed formamide on TiO2 under 3.2 eV irradiation yields guanine through semiconductor-assisted photochemistry.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Impact/plasma formamide route", "description": "High-energy proton or plasma processing of formamide produces guanine through CN radical chemistry.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "HCN-to-FaPy-to-guanosine pathway", "description": "HCN and formic acid feed FaPy precursor formation; activated FaPy condenses with ribose to guanosine, providing a target-reaching nucleoside route that embeds guanine chemistry on sugar.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_014", "rxn_015", "rxn_013", "rxn_016"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_018", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Classical guanine followed by direct glycosylation", "description": "Base-first chemistry yields guanine via AICA/cyanogen branch, then ribose couples inefficiently to give guanosine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_013", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_010", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Guanosine phosphorylation to nucleotide", "description": "FaPy-derived guanosine is phosphorylated to GMP in biochemical/prebiotic pools, completing incorporation of guanine into nucleotide space.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_014", "rxn_015", "rxn_013", "rxn_016", "rxn_018"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_018", "mol_021", "mol_023"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_004", "mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_010", "mol_015"], "convergence_points": [{"molecule_id": "mol_004", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_002"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_003", "rxn_014"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_008", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_004"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_005"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_010", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_005"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_014", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_017"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_015", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_013"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_016", "rxn_017"]}]}, "reasoning": "", "duration_ms": 130293.383121